%N A396024 Decimal expansion of 2/3 + 2*(2 - sqrt(3))/Pi.
%C A396024 The probability that Buffon's needle (see A060294) will land on a line when dropped onto a floor with parallel lines spaced at a distance equal to half the length of the needle.
%C A396024 In general, if x is the ratio between the length of the needle and the separation distance between the lines, then the probability is 2*x/Pi if x <= 1, and (2/Pi)*(arccos(1/x) + x - sqrt(x^2-1)) otherwise.
%H A396024 Emanuel Czuber, <a href="https://archive.org/details/geometwahrschein00czubrich/page/n103/mode/1up">Geometrische Wahrscheinlichkeiten und Mittelwerte</a>, B. G. Teubner, Leipzig, 1884, pp. 159-160.
%H A396024 Persi Diaconis, <a href="https://doi.org/10.2307/3212484">Buffon's problem with a long needle</a>, Journal of Applied Probability, Vol. 13, No. 3 (1976), pp. 614-618; <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20090625180244id_/http://www-stat.stanford.edu/~cgates/PERSI/papers/needle.pdf">alternative link</a>.
%H A396024 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/BuffonsNeedleProblem.html">Buffon's needle problem</a>.
%H A396024 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Buffon&#39;s_needle_problem">Buffon's needle problem</a>.
%H A396024 <a href="/index/Tra#transcendental">Index entries for transcendental numbers</a>.
